        {
            "title": "Momentum Behind EVs Over Hybrids",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><div class=\"akcelo-wrapper akcelo-video media--169\" style=\"width:100%\"><div class=\"border:solid 1px #C0C0C0\" id=\"Zonebourse_Article_Video\" video-id=\"k3agWshpg8LqrTDXGao\"><div itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"https://schema.org/VideoObject\"><meta content=\"Momentum Behind EVs Over Hybrids\" itemprop=\"name\"/><meta content=\"Jon McNeill, CEO and Co-founder at DVx Ventures who is also a member at GM's Board of directors says that hybrids will fade over time as EV technology advances. He also says Chinese EVs are &quot;heavily subsidized&quot; and raise data-security questions, making US entry unlikely without tough trade negotiations. He spoke with Scarlet Fu on &quot;Bloomberg Markets.&quot;\n\" itemprop=\"description\"/><meta content=\"2025-10-02T22:20:58+02:00\" itemprop=\"uploadDate\"/><meta content=\"/images/mtnewswires/A3469311.png\" itemprop=\"thumbnailUrl\"/><meta content=\"https://geo.dailymotion.com/player/x80uo.html?video=k3agWshpg8LqrTDXGao\" itemprop=\"embedUrl\"/></div></div></div>\n               Jon McNeill, CEO and Co-founder at DVx Ventures who is also a member at GM's Board of directors says that hybrids will fade over time as EV technology advances. He also says Chinese EVs are \"heavily subsidized\" and raise data-security questions, making US entry unlikely without tough trade negotiations. He spoke with Scarlet Fu on \"Bloomberg Markets.\"<p><span class=\"js-l-obf link link--blue\" data-lobf=\"v4fox4ar=NTQyQxJmBMKwpP7nl8C=BbKwgTpvkfAwLuu\" data-tobf=\"blank\" onclick=\"gaEvent('Out', 'mtnewswires', '51247818');\">Bloomberg videos</span>, provided by MT Newswires</p></div>",
